name: ISUOG
overview:
ISUOG has been in existence since 1991 and, with over 6,000 members in 125 countries, it is the most important society in this medical specialty and provides its membership with educational opportunities in the ever developing field of ultrasound in obstetrics and gynecology.

ISUOG services its members through its annual World Congress, attracting around 1,200 delegates; educational approved courses; and its peer-reviewed research journal Ultrasound in Obstetrics & Gynecology which is circulated to over 4,000 destinations worldwide. The ISUOG website also features an ever increasing number of educational resources for members including CD Roms and web lectures.

ISUOG’s World Congress is held in the Autumn of each year. The event provides attendees with the opportunity to learn, review and update clinical and technical knowledge, as well as compare and relate ultrasound knowledge and skills with peers and industry experts. It is also the perfect opportunity to keep abreast of industry issues by networking with ultrasound professionals and meet with suppliers and manufacturers in the ultrasound industry.
